cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on text summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The use of statistical and semantic techniques for summarization suggests that this paper could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the inclusion of sentiment analysis suggests a potential connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of a hybrid model incorporating multiple techniques suggests a potential connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
